meanings.definition: To exhaust or tire out by physical exertion.
meanings.sent1: After running the marathon, he felt completely outwinded.
meanings.sent2: She outwinded herself by climbing to the top of the mountain.
meanings.sent3: The energetic puppy quickly outwinded its owner during the long walk.
meanings.sent4: The intense workout outwinded her more than she expected.
meanings.sent5: The relentless heat outwinded the hikers as they trekked through the desert.

meanings.definition: To surpass or outdo in endurance or stamina.
meanings.sent1: In the race, he managed to outwind his competitors and reach the finish line first.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outwinded all expectations by completing the triathlon with ease.
meanings.sent3: The determined squirrel outwinded the others in gathering nuts for the winter.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication to training allowed her to outwind her previous record time.
meanings.sent5: The champion boxer outwinded his opponent with his superior strength and skill.
